Assistant: Absolutely! Here are some practical examples to help you out:

**Docker Command to Start Worker Script**:

```yaml
docker run \
    -e FRANKENPHP_CONFIG="worker /app/path/to/your/worker/script.php" \
    -v $PWD:/app \
    -p 80:80 -p 443:443 -p 443:443/udp \
    dunglas/frankenphp
```

This snippet shows you how to docker command to start worker script, which is an important aspect of using frankenphp workers.

**Standalone Binary Command to Start Worker Script**:

```yaml
frankenphp php-server --worker /path/to/your/worker/script.php
```

This snippet shows you how to standalone binary command to start worker script, which is an important aspect of using frankenphp workers.

